headline: YUM Q1 Earnings Call: Digital Investments and Global Expansion Drive Mixed Results
summary: Fast-food company Yum! Brands (NYSE:YUM) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q1 CY2025, but sales rose 11.8% year on year to $1.79 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.30 per share was 1.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
